info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Computes an operation between the values in the same position of multiple input measures. 

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are a list of:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure : input measure. This argument can be specified multiple times.
- operation name: type of operation
                    -- 'oph_sum' : compute the sum of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_avg' : compute the average of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_mul' : compute the product of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_max' : compute the maximum of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_min' : compute the minimum of the elements;
                    -- 'oph_arg_max' : return the index of the position associated with the minimum value;
                    -- 'oph_arg_min' : return the index of the position associated with the minimum value.
- missingvalue : value to be considered as missing value (set it to NULL if not given);
                 by default it is NAN (for 'oph_double' and 'oph_float').

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
oph_operation_array('OPH_DOUBLE|OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',a.measure,b.measure,'OPH_MAX',NULL)
